Introduction:
Dear participant,

As a marketing expert, your task is to critically evaluate a number of texts on their level of "Fluff". 
In this context, "Fluff" refers to any content that is unnecessary, lacks substance, or does not directly contribute to the main message or purpose of a given text. 

To guide you through your evaluations, you are provided with a list of text characteristics that typically indicate fluff. 

Take your time to read each text carefully before scoring each characteristic. In the end you are asked to provide one overall fluff score and a short reason for each text. 

The core survey consists of 10 texts, but to accomodate for your availability you will be given the option to exit the survey early after 6 texts and each additional evaluation. 

Your answers will be anonymized.

Thank you for participating in this survey and thereby contributing to this research.
Fabian Sauer

- Agree to provide answers to the best of your ability.
